{
  "text": "Cells were washed two times with PBS and incubated with 50 \u00b5M monochlorobimane (MCB) for 45 minutes as described previously [CITATION_1] . Subsequently the cells were trypsinsed and stained with 1 \u00b5g/ml propidium iodide (PI). The samples were analyzed in a FACS DIVA flow cytometer (Becton Dickinson, USA) equipped with one argon (Spectra Physics, USA) and one krypton laser (Coherent, USA) tuned to 488 nm and UV, respectively. Figure 1 Lamp spectra. A) The UVA lamp has a peak at 375 nm. Total UVA-irradiance (320-400 nm) was 436 W/m 2 . B) The UVB lamp has a peak at 312 nm. Total UVB-irradiance (290-320 nm) was 23. ",
